{{Expand Norwegian|date=January 2011|Christopher Brinchmann}} [[File:ChristoferBrinchmann.jpg|thumb|Christopher Brinchmann]]
'''Christopher Brinchmann''' (1 April 1864 – 26 February 1940) was a Norwegian archivist, literary historian and critic.<ref>{{cite web|url= https://lokalhistoriewiki.no/index.php/Christopher_Brinchmann |title= Christopher Brinchmann |publisher = lokalhistoriewiki.no|accessdate= January 1, 2017}}</ref>
He was born at [[Leka, Norway|Leka]] in [[Nord-Trøndelag]], Norway. He worked in the [[National Archival Services of Norway]] (''Riksarkivet'') from 1896, and was deputy director from 1922 to 1934. He was among the publishers of ''[[Diplomatarium Norvegicum]]''. Among his own works were ''Nationalforskeren P. A. Munch; hans liv og virke'' (1910), ''Grønlands overgang til Danmark'' (1922), ''Norske kongesigiller'' (1924) and ''Norges arkivsaker i Danmark'' (1927). He also edited the periodical ''[[Kringsjaa]]'', from 1898 to 1907.<ref>{{cite web|url= https://snl.no/Riksarkivet |title= Riksarkivet|publisher = lokalhistoriewiki.no|accessdate= January 1, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url= http://arkivverket.no/arkivverket/Arkivverket/Om-oss/Aktuelt/Nyhetsarkiv/Nyhetsarkiv-2011/Diplomatarium-Norvegicum |title= Diplomatarium Norvegicum |publisher= Arkivverket|accessdate= January 1, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url= https://snl.no/Diplomatarium_Norvegicum |title= Diplomatarium Norvegicum |publisher = Store norske leksikon |accessdate= January 1, 2017}}</ref><ref name=snl>{{cite encyclopedia |year=2007 |title=Brinchmann, Christopher |encyclopedia=[[Store norske leksikon]] |publisher=Kunnskapsforlaget |location= |url= http://www.snl.no/Christopher_Brinchmann }}</ref>
