{{Infobox scientist | name = Karo Ghafadaryan | image = <!--(filename only, i.e. without "File:" prefix)--> | imagesize = | caption = | birth_date = {{birth date |1907|04|20}} | birth_place = [[Akhaltsikhe]], [[Tiflis Governorate]], Russian Empire (present-day [[Samtskhe-Javakheti]], [[Georgia (country)|Georgia]] | death_date = {{death date and age|1976|12|21|1907|04|20}} | death_place = [[Yerevan]], Armenian SSR, Soviet Union | nationality = Armenian | fields = History | workplaces = | alma_mater = [[Yerevan State University]] | doctoral_advisor = | academic_advisors = | doctoral_students = | notable_students = | awards = Honored Worker of Science of the Armenian SSR (1961)<ref name="SAE">{{cite book|first=Aram|last=Ghanalanyan|contribution=Ղաֆադարյան Կարո [Ghafadaryan Karo]|title=[[Soviet Armenian Encyclopedia]]|publisher=Armenian Encyclopedia|volume=7|page=[http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/95/%D5%80%D5%A1%D5%B5%D5%AF%D5%A1%D5%AF%D5%A1%D5%B6_%D5%8D%D5%B8%D5%BE%D5%A5%D5%BF%D5%A1%D5%AF%D5%A1%D5%B6_%D5%80%D5%A1%D5%B6%D6%80%D5%A1%D5%A3%D5%AB%D5%BF%D5%A1%D6%80%D5%A1%D5%B6_%28Soviet_Armenian_Encyclopedia%29_7.djvu/page38-4417px-%D5%80%D5%A1%D5%B5%D5%AF%D5%A1%D5%AF%D5%A1%D5%B6_%D5%8D%D5%B8%D5%BE%D5%A5%D5%BF%D5%A1%D5%AF%D5%A1%D5%B6_%D5%80%D5%A1%D5%B6%D6%80%D5%A1%D5%A3%D5%AB%D5%BF%D5%A1%D6%80%D5%A1%D5%B6_%28Soviet_Armenian_Encyclopedia%29_7.djvu.jpg 38]|language=hy|location=Yerevan}}</ref> }}
'''Karo Ghafadaryan''' ({{lang-hy|Կարո Ղաֆադարյան}}; April 20, 1907{{spaced ndash}}December 21, 1976) was a Soviet Armenian [[archaeologist]], [[historian]], [[epigraphist]], [[philologist]].<ref name="SAE"/><ref name="PBH">{{cite journal|last=Arakelian|first=Babken|authorlink=Babken Arakelyan|title=Կարո Ղաֆադարյան [Karo Ghafadarian]|journal=[[Patma-Banasirakan Handes]]|date=1976|issue=4|pages=249–250|url=http://hpj.asj-oa.am/2681/|publisher=[[Armenian Academy of Sciences]]|location=Yerevan|language=hy}}</ref> He was the director of the [[History Museum of Armenia]] (1940–1965).<ref name="SAE"/> "Under his guidance, the Museum became an advanced research and cultural-educational centre" in Armenia.<ref name="historymuseum">{{cite web|title=Notable Personalities > Karo Ghafadarian |url=http://www.historymuseum.am/museum/?id=3&lang=eng |publisher=History Museum of Armenia |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140915183755/http://www.historymuseum.am/museum/?id=3&lang=eng |archivedate=September 15, 2014 }}</ref>
Born in [[Akhaltsikhe]], he graduated from the [[Yerevan State University]] in 1931. Since 1932 he worked at the Institute of Culture History and took part in the excavations of [[Shengavit Settlement|Shengavit]], [[Vagharshapat]] and other ancient locations. He supervised the excavations of the ruins of the medieval Armenian capital of [[Dvin (ancient city)|Dvin]] for around three decades. Since 1959 until his death he headed the department of medieval archaeology of the Armenian Academy of Sciences.<ref name="SAE"/>
<!-- http://www.ysu.am/retro_gallery/hy/1380710118/page/3 -->
