{{Infobox economist | name = Lance E. Davis | native_name = | native_name_lang = | school_tradition = | color = | image = | image_size = | caption = | birth_date = {{birth date|1928|11|03}} | birth_place = [[Seattle]] | death_date = {{death date and age|2014|01|20|1928|11|03}} | death_place = | resting_place = | resting_place_coordinates = | nationality = | institution = [[California Institute of Technology]] | field = | alma_mater = [[Johns Hopkins University]] | influences = | influenced = | contributions = | awards = | memorials = | spouse = | signature = <!-- file name only --> | module = | repec_prefix = | repec_id = }} '''Lance Edwin Davis''' (November 3, 1928<ref>{{Cite book | last1 = Engerman | first1 = S. L. | authorlink1 = Stanley Engerman| last2 = Hoffman | first2 = P. T. | last3 = Rosenthal | first3 = J. L. | last4 = Sokoloff | first4 = K. L. | chapter = Afterword: About Lance Davis | doi = 10.1017/CBO9780511510892.013 | title = Finance, Intermediaries, and Economic Development | pages = 319 | year = 2003 | isbn = 9780511510892 | pmid = | pmc = }}</ref> – January 20, 2014) was the Mary Stillman Harkness Professor of Social Science at the [[California Institute of Technology]]. He researched the economic history of financial markets and institutional and technological change. His work has been recognised by [[The Cliometric Society]] via their awarding him a ''Clio Can'' in recognition his ''of exceptional support of [[cliometrics]]''.<ref>[http://www.hss.caltech.edu/people/led/profile Caltech: Lance E. Davis] (Accessed Dec 2011)</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.pasadenanow.com/main/caltech-professor-lance-e-davis-dies-at-85 |title=Pasadena Now » Caltech Social Science Professor Lance E. Davis Dies at 85 |publisher=PasadenaNow.com |date= |accessdate=2014-01-27}}</ref>
Davis was also a research associate at the [[National Bureau of Economic Research]].<ref>[http://www.nber.org/people/lance_davis National Bureau of Economic Research: Lance E. Davis] (Accessed Dec 2011)</ref> He earned a [[Doctor of Philosophy|PhD]] from [[Johns Hopkins University]] in 1956 with thesis titled ''United States Financial Intermediaries in the Early 19th Century: Four Case Studies''.<ref>{{cite web | title = United States Financial Intermediaries in the Early 19th Century: Four Case Studies | url = http://search.proquest.com/docview/301921622/ | first = Lance E. | last = Davis | publisher = ProQuest | accessdate = January 23, 2014}}</ref>
==Selected publications== * Davis, Lance E. with Douglass North (1971) Institutional Change and American Economic Growth, Cambridge University Press. * Davis, Lance E. with Robert Huttenback (1986) Mammon and the Pursuit of Empire: The Political Economy of British Imperialism (revised and abridged edition, 1988), Cambridge University Press. * Davis, Lance E. with Robert Cull(1994) International Capital Markets and American Economic Growth, 1820–1914, Cambridge University Press. * Davis, Lance E. with Robert Gallman (200) Evolving Financial Markets and International Capital Flows: Britain, the Americas, and Australia, 1870–1914, Cambridge University Press.
