{{Quote box | quote = ''"I have just come home from [[Port Said]], after successfully commanding a slow speed laden bulk carrier through the Gulf of Aden. We followed the courses through the MSPA (Maritime Security Patrol Area) corridor, which is patrolled by naval fleet. It was a very tense 40-hour passage. We witnessed an attempted attack just 10 miles behind us, one successful hijacking and another two attempts just close."'' --Captain Vinayak Anant Marathe, India (2008) | source =<ref name="bbc">{{cite news|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/middle_east/7736170.stm|title=Capt Vinayak Anant Marathe, India|date=18 November 2008|publisher=bbc.co.uk|accessdate=2008-12-05}}</ref> | width =30% | align =right }} The '''Maritime Security Patrol Area''' ('''MSPA''') is a specified patrol zone in the [[Gulf of Aden]] and [[Guardafui Channel]]. Its borders are unmarked, but are a narrow, rectangular corridor between [[Somalia]] and [[Yemen]], within the northern sector of the gulf. The MSPA was established 22 August 2008 by the [[Combined Task Force 150]], (CTF-150) a multinational, coalition naval task force in order to deter de-stabilizing activities, including [[piracy]] within this [[maritime geographical]] area. The establishment of the MSPA was directed by the Commander, [[United States Central Command|United States Naval Central Command]].<ref name="newsletterscience">{{cite web|url=http://www.newsletterscience.com/marex/readmore.cgi?issue_id=320&article_id=3469&l=%3C|title=Maritime Security Patrol Area (MSPA) in the Gulf of Aden Established|publisher=newsletterscience.com|accessdate=2008-11-30|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110714174255/http://www.newsletterscience.com/marex/readmore.cgi?issue_id=320&article_id=3469&l=%3C|archivedate=2011-07-14|df=}}</ref><ref name="icc">{{cite news|url=http://www.icc-ccs.org/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=163:coalition-warships-set-up-maritime-security-patrol-area-in-the-gulf-of-aden&catid=60:news|title= Coalition warships set up Maritime Security Patrol area in the Gulf of Aden|date=26 August 2008 |publisher=icc-ccs.org|accessdate=2008-11-30}}</ref><ref name="cusnc">{{cite news|url=http://www.cusnc.navy.mil/articles/2008/115.html |title=Combined Task Force 150 Thwarts Criminal Activities |date=September 22, 2008 |publisher=cusnc.navy.mil |accessdate=2008-11-30 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20081028074107/http://www.cusnc.navy.mil/articles/2008/115.html |archivedate=October 28, 2008 |df= }}</ref><ref name="eaglespeak">{{cite web|url=http://www.eaglespeak.us/2008/08/gulf-of-aden-martime-security-zone.html|title=Gulf of Aden Martime {{sic|hide=y|reason=spelling error in source}} Security Zone|date=August 31, 2008|publisher=eaglespeak.us|accessdate=2008-12-04}}</ref><ref name="simsl">{{cite web|url=http://www.simsl.com/PiracySomaliaGulfAden1108.html|title=Piracy - Somalia and Gulf of Aden|date=November 2008|publisher=simsl.com|accessdate=2008-12-04}}</ref>
